    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.jpeg</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>
    



    <ingredient>4 cups cherry tomatos halved</ingredient>
    <ingredient>3 cloves garlic minced </ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 TBsp olive oil </ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/4 teaspoon Salt and Pepper</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 cup feta crumbled</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 bunch dill chopped</ingredient>

    <step>
Preheat oven to 180C while preparing the ingredients. In shallow baking dish place all ingredients. Cook for 30-40 mins. When tomatoes have all collapsed remove from oven. Stir and sprinkle with additional dill if desired.  Serve with BBQ meat.

* different variety tomatos can be used, I prefer 2 red and 1 yellow punnet
    </step>
</recipe>